.TH "tb_domain_alloc" 9 "tb_domain_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_domain_alloc \- Allocate a domain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tb *" tb_domain_alloc
.BI "(struct tb_nhi *nhi "  ","
.BI "size_t privsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nhi" 12
Pointer to the host controller
.IP "privsize" 12
Size of the connection manager private data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates and initializes a new Thunderbolt domain. Connection
managers are expected to call this and then fill in \fIcm_ops\fP
accordingly.

Call \fBtb_domain_put\fP to release the domain before it has been added
to the system.
.SH "RETURN"
allocated domain structure on NULL in case of error
